      <Fragment slot="scrollspy-content">
        <div id="intro" class="story-top-scroll">
          <h1 class="text-start">How to Center a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code></h1>
          <h5><a href="/media/pdf/How To Center a _div_.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><i class="bi bi-filetype-pdf"></i> PDF Download</a></h5><br>
          <h5><b>Made & Published by:</b> <a href="/">AT Products LLC</a>.</h5>
          <h5><b>Published on:</b> October 23rd, 2024.</h5>
          <br>
          <p>This article contains information on how to center a <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> using CSS, horizontally and vertically, within HTML. The sole purpose of this article is to annoy <a href="https://github.com/VenenJean">Venen Jean</a>, so have fun with this little payback.</p>
          <hr>
        </div>
        <div id="horizontal">
          <h2>Horizontally Aligning</h2>
          <p>Horizontally aligning a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> is more easier than vertically aligning a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>.</p>
          <h3>Auto Margin</h3>
          <p>A margin sets the space outside the selected element. Setting the element's left and right margin to auto, automatically makes it centered horizontally. </p>
          <p>Your code should contain <code>margin-left: auto;</code> and <code>margin-right: auto;</code>, and its <code>display</code> must be set to <code>block</code> using <code>display: block;</code>. <a href="#source-1" class="fw-bold">[1]</a></p>
          <iframe height="300" style="width: 100%;" scrolling="no" title="Centering a image in all directions." src="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/embed/bGXqrZY?default-tab=css%2Cresult" frameborder="no" loading="lazy" allowtransparency="true" allowfullscreen="true">
            See the Pen <a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/pen/bGXqrZY">
            Centering a image in all directions.</a> by Alex-Toucan (<a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan">@alex-toucan</a>)
            on <a href="https://codepen.io">CodePen</a>.
          </iframe>
          <h3>Flexbox</h3>
          <p>You can also use Flexbox to center your &lt;div&gt; using <code>display: flex;</code> and <code>justify-content: center;</code>. <a href="#source-4" class="fw-bold">[4]</a></p>
          <iframe height="300" style="width: 100%;" scrolling="no" title="Centering a div in a horizontal direction." src="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/embed/RwXpQJj?default-tab=css%2Cresult" frameborder="no" loading="lazy" allowtransparency="true" allowfullscreen="true">
            See the Pen <a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/pen/RwXpQJj">
            Centering a div in a horizontal direction.</a> by Alex-Toucan (<a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan">@alex-toucan</a>)
            on <a href="https://codepen.io">CodePen</a>.
          </iframe>
          <h3>Text Center</h3>
          <p>To center not necessarily a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>, but any text, use <code>text-align: center;</code> for its property. <a href="#source-1" class="fw-bold">[1]</a></p>
          <iframe height="300" style="width: 100%;" scrolling="no" title="Centering text in a horizontal direction." src="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/embed/bGXqLLx?default-tab=css%2Cresult" frameborder="no" loading="lazy" allowtransparency="true" allowfullscreen="true">
            See the Pen <a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/pen/bGXqLLx">
            Centering text in a horizontal direction.</a> by Alex-Toucan (<a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan">@alex-toucan</a>)
            on <a href="https://codepen.io">CodePen</a>.
          </iframe>
        </div>
        <div id="vertical">
          <h2>Vertically Aligning</h2>
          <p>Vertically aligning a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> is harder than horizontally aligning.</p>
          <h3>Using Position and Transform</h3>
          <p>Combining <code>position: relative;</code> for your parent container, and using <code>position: absolute;</code>, <code>top: 50%;</code>, and <code>transform: translateY(-50%);</code> for your child container. This can align the child's container in a vertical direction. <a href="#source-2" class="fw-bold">[2]</a></p>
          <iframe height="300" style="width: 100%;" scrolling="no" title="Centering text in a vertical direction using position." src="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/embed/JjgWpgN?default-tab=css%2Cresult" frameborder="no" loading="lazy" allowtransparency="true" allowfullscreen="true">
            See the Pen <a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/pen/JjgWpgN">
            Centering text in a vertical direction using position.</a> by Alex-Toucan (<a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan">@alex-toucan</a>)
            on <a href="https://codepen.io">CodePen</a>.
          </iframe>
          <h3>Padding</h3>
          <p>Top and bottom padding can vertically center text. <a href="#source-1" class="fw-bold">[1]</a></p>
          <iframe height="300" style="width: 100%;" scrolling="no" title="Centering text in a vertical direction using padding." src="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/embed/mdNWXGX?default-tab=css%2Cresult" frameborder="no" loading="lazy" allowtransparency="true" allowfullscreen="true">
            See the Pen <a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/pen/mdNWXGX">
            Centering text in a vertical direction using padding.</a> by Alex-Toucan (<a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan">@alex-toucan</a>)
            on <a href="https://codepen.io">CodePen</a>.
          </iframe>
          <h3>Line Height</h3>
          <p>For <code>line-height</code> to vertically align text, it must be the same height as the container. If your text is above one line, you can use <code>line-height: 1.5;</code> on the <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> tag. <a href="#source-1" class="fw-bold">[1]</a></p>
          <iframe height="300" style="width: 100%;" scrolling="no" title="Centering text in a vertical direction using line height." src="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/embed/JjgWpgN?default-tab=css%2Cresult" frameborder="no" loading="lazy" allowtransparency="true" allowfullscreen="true">
            See the Pen <a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/pen/JjgWpgN">
            Centering text in a vertical direction using line height.</a> by Alex-Toucan (<a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan">@alex-toucan</a>)
            on <a href="https://codepen.io">CodePen</a>.
          </iframe>
        </div>
        <div id="both">
          <h2>Aligning in Both Directions</h2>
          <p>This section will show how a &lt;div&gt; can be both horizontally and vertically aligned.</p>
          <h3>Flexbox</h3>
          <p>You can use Flexbox to center your &lt;div&gt; using <code>display: flex;</code>, <code>justify-content: center;</code>, <code>align-items: center;</code>, and setting a <code>height</code> on a parent container. <a href="#source-4" class="fw-bold">[4]</a></p>
          <iframe height="300" style="width: 100%;" scrolling="no" title="Centering a div in all directions." src="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/embed/OJKpQww?default-tab=css%2Cresult" frameborder="no" loading="lazy" allowtransparency="true" allowfullscreen="true">
            See the Pen <a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/pen/OJKpQww">
            Centering a div in all directions.</a> by Alex-Toucan (<a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan">@alex-toucan</a>)
            on <a href="https://codepen.io">CodePen</a>.
          </iframe>
          <h3>Using Position and Transform</h3>
          <p>Combining <code>position: relative;</code> for your parent container, and using <code>position: absolute;</code>, <code>top: 50%;</code>, <code>left: 50%;</code>, and <code>transform: translate(-50%, -50%);</code> for your child container. This can align the child's container in all directions. <a href="#source-2" class="fw-bold">[2]</a></p>
          <iframe height="300" style="width: 100%;" scrolling="no" title="Centering text in all directions using line height." src="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/embed/VwopQgM?default-tab=css%2Cresult" frameborder="no" loading="lazy" allowtransparency="true" allowfullscreen="true">
            See the Pen <a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/pen/VwopQgM">
            Centering position in all directions using position.</a> by Alex-Toucan (<a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan">@alex-toucan</a>)
            on <a href="https://codepen.io">CodePen</a>.
          </iframe>
          <h3>Padding</h3>
          <p>Top and bottom padding, combined with <code>text-align: center;</code>, can horizontally and vertically align text. <a href="#source-1" class="fw-bold">[1]</a></p>
          <iframe height="300" style="width: 100%;" scrolling="no" title="Centering text in all directions using padding." src="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/embed/bGXqLmQ?default-tab=css%2Cresult" frameborder="no" loading="lazy" allowtransparency="true" allowfullscreen="true">
            See the Pen <a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/pen/bGXqLmQ">
            Centering text in all directions using padding.</a> by Alex-Toucan (<a href="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan">@alex-toucan</a>)
            on <a href="https://codepen.io">CodePen</a>.
          </iframe>
          <h3>Line Height</h3>
          <p>For <code>line-height</code> to vertically align text, it must be the same height as the container. You can also combine this with <code>text-align: center;</code>. If your text is above one line, you can use <code>line-height: 1.5;</code> on the <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> tag. <a href="#source-1" class="fw-bold">[1]</a></p>
          <iframe height="300" style="width: 100%;" scrolling="no" title="Centering text in all directions using line height." src="https://codepen.io/alex-toucan/embed/wvVJyRQ?default-tab=css%2Cresult" frameborder="no" loading="lazy" allowtransparency="true" allowfullscreen="true">
